cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite both the software itself (using the metadata below) and the accompanying peer-reviewed paper (see 'preferred-citation')."
type: software
title: "SimilCode Frontend"
abstract: >
  React 18.2 web interface for the SimilCode source-code similarity
  analysis system. Provides the instructor-facing workflow for
  submitting code pairs, selecting the analysis model (Claude Opus 4.1,
  GPT-5, Gemini 2.5 Pro, or DeepSeek-V3), and consuming multidimensional
  similarity scores, human-readable justifications, and Big O
  complexity estimates returned by the backend API. Designed as a
  screening aid for academic-integrity workflows in resource-constrained
  higher-education institutions. Supported source languages in this
  release: C# and Java.
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-07-07"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/gleiston-guerrero/FrontEnd-SimilCode"
url: "https://github.com/gleiston-guerrero/FrontEnd-SimilCode"
